			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="471">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Thanks for reprinting excerpts&nbsp;from the Hillman interviews and Michael Ventura&rsquo;s wise and witty essay [&ldquo;<a href="/article/4680">James Hillman Never Said Hello to Me</a>,&rdquo; July 2012]. Hillman&rsquo;s critical approach to American self-help culture and family-history-obsessed psychology reminds me why I&rsquo;m annoyed by the endings of so many stories printed in <em>The Sun</em>. The Readers Write section especially seems prone to moralistic memoir in which the present is justified or understood or accepted by unlocking or confessing a past hurt. Such poignant conclusions tie up what Hillman might encourage us to unravel.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Keith Hennessy<br>San Francisco, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

